Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes an event-based metering strategy for electricity demand data, which can be considered a control problem. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method to set the thresholds from the percentage of the peak power consumption can be seen as a machine learning approach. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Similar to the previous reasoning, the proposed method can be considered a machine learning approach. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper deals with a practical problem related to electricity demand data, which can be considered a computational engineering problem. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed method can have implications for data privacy and security in the context of electricity demand data.
